review_blob: Bottle - reminds me of Ricards Red.  Not great but not bad either.  The aroma wasnt offensive.  Sweet aftertaste
beer_name: Great Lakes Brewing Red Leaf Lager

review_blob: Bottle - looked good in the glass and ringed well.  Although I am not a great fan Darks, I was surprised at the drinkability of Black Jack.  Found the body to be medium and the aftertaste was not objectionable.
beer_name: Great Lakes Brewing Black Jack Lager

review_blob: Not the best Pilsner Ive enjoyed.  M.O.R.  Had a slight skunky taste but might have been light struck at the Beer Store.  Great brewery under the CN TowerI hope they dont get the water from Lake Ontario!

With all the Honey Browns out there this one is actually quite good.  Its not a buck a beer but for good reason.  A great job by small brewery.  I think it would taste even better on a dock in Muskoka...oh ya...I dont have one of those.  Ill settle for this good tasting beer.

After cracking open this very expensive beer in its very expensive box I was very surprised at the smell of dirty socks- this last batch.  I am not sure whose idea it was to add the "sea-monkeys" or whatever was floating in the bottle, but you might want to re-think that one!  I have tasted this beer on several occasions and be sure that it keeps you guessing as consistency isnt in the recipe.  Id like to recommend visiting the very expensive looking brewery and store but nothing new has been added in the past year or so.  Disappointed that there was nothing new to see or buy.  Too expensive  actually over priced for what you actually get  just like their Ale.
